-- FCC Says Rick Kaplan to Succeed Bruce Gottlieb as Agency's Chief Counsel
-- Bill Koenig
-- 2010-07-06T18:21:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/fcc-says-rick-kaplan-to-succeed-bruce-gottlieb-as-agency-s-chief-counsel.html

          
          
              The Federal Communications
Commission named Rick Kaplan as chief counsel and senior legal
advisor.  
 He succeeds Bruce Gottlieb, who will be leaving the
commission at the end of July, the agency said in an e-mailed
statement.  
          
          


  


        